    "::: {.callout-important}\n",
    "## 🤔 Discussion Questions: Stage 3 - Structuring of Visual Mappings\n",
    "\n",
    "**Question 1: Geometry Choices**\n",
    "- Why is a horizontal bar chart better than a scatter plot for this data?\n",
    "<br>\n",
    "A horizontal bar chart is better than a scatter plot for this data because it is easier to compare the performance of different stadiums across a season. A scatter plot would not be as easy to compare because it would be difficult to see the difference between the performance of different stadiums.\n",
    "- When would you choose a vertical bar chart over horizontal?\n",
    "<br>\n",
    "A vertical bar chart would be better than a horizontal bar chart when you want to compare the performance of different stadiums across a season. \n",
    "**Question 2: Aesthetic Mappings**\n",
    "- What does the color highlighting accomplish in Approach 4?\n",
    "- How does position (x/y) compare to color for encoding data?\n",
    "<br>\n",
    "The color highlighting in Approach 4 accomplishes the goal of highlighting Coors Field as the most run-friendly ballpark in 2010. The position (x/y) is used to highlight the ordinality of the data. (If you are higher up on the y-axis, you are more run-friendly than if you are lower on the y-axis.)\n",
    "\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "## Stage 4: Formatting for Your Audience\n",
    "\n",
    "**Mental Model:** Polish your visualization for professional presentation.\n",
    "\n",
