   "source": [
    "::: {.callout-important}\n",
    "## 🤔 Discussion Questions: Stage 4 - Formatting for Your Audience\n",
    "\n",
    "**Question 1: Professional Formatting**\n",
    "- What elements make this visualization suitable for a business presentation?\n",
    "- Is the annotation on the visualization helpful?  Can you fix its placement?\n",
    "<br>\n",
    "The visualization is suitable for a business presentation because it is professional and easy to understand. The coloring of COL is helpful because it instantly makes the point of the graph jump out at the reader: COL is the most run friendly park in 2010. Additionally, The way we use y axis positioning is extremely intuitive, making the graph do most of the work, not necessarily the reader. The annotation is helpful because it gives extra information to the reader about the stadium we care about the most: Colorado..\n",
    "\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Advanced Object-Oriented Techniques\n",
    "\n",
    "**Mental Model:** Use object-oriented matplotlib to create complex, reusable visualizations.\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's create a comprehensive comparison between 2010 and 2021:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "advanced-oo-techniques",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#| label: advanced-oo-techniques\n",
    "#| echo: true\n",
    "\n",
    "# Advanced Object-Oriented Techniques\n",
    "# Create a comprehensive comparison visualization\n",
    "\n",
    "# Prepare data for comparison\n",
    "comparison_data = pd.merge(\n",
    "    avgDF_2010[['home', 'totalRuns']].rename(columns={'totalRuns': 'runs_2010'}),\n",
